They look like a row of Hobbit holes but these inventive rooms at a hotel in the Netherlands are in fact giant wine barrels.

The Hotel de Vrouwe van Stavoren has installed four 15,000-litre capacity dark wooden vats in its backyard, giving the term B&B a new meaning - booze & bed.

