The barrels were imported to the guesthouse in north-west Netherlands from Switzerland in 1981 and eight larger ones are to be brought from France next year.

These new casks will be nearly 50 per cent bigger again as they can hold up to a staggering 22,000 litres.

Overlooking the picturesque old harbour of Stavoren, the B&B enjoys stunning views of the huge artificial Lake IJsselmeer and the wooden ships that are moored there.

It also boasts a restaurant specialising in dishes using local fish and is surrounded by beautiful bright red and pastel pink flowers.

